record.text: Love a brave baritone

A piano player I've sung with has a comment about how you can just say "Oh, I'm no one's wife, but oh, I love my life and all that jazz" on beat to the tune and you're doing as much singing as Rex Harrison or Richard Burton ever did and they won Tonys.

I'm a true bass. I can't read music, but I can transpose on the fly very quickly and easily because people in low registers can't sing most popular music unless we learn.

I can do "You're a mean one, Mr. Grinch" in its original register, but my chest voice only goes up to about middle C.
And thanks to lung disease, I very rarely have usable head voice. It's choked off.

I thought about pushing back on that title with something like Modern Major General, but I can't dispute Sondheim. 

And i doubt I could pull off either of them anymore!
